    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I don't believe [DataFrame.nsmallest](https://pandas.pydata.org/pandas-docs/stable/generated/pandas.DataFrame.nsmallest.html) will provide the behavior you're looking for.  The `column` arg is **Column name or names to order by**\r\n\r\nTo illustrate\r\n```\r\n dummy = df.nsmallest(n = 1, columns=['c','a','b'])\r\n print(dummy)\r\n   a  b  c\r\n1  9  1  0\r\n```\r\nMaybe `df.min()` is what you're after?"
  },
