    "body": "Thanks for your answer @bobhaffner. Obviously the nsmallest method is not doing what I need. The example above was just to illustrate the actual behaviour.\r\nImagine now that you need to take the mean value between the 4 smallest numbers for each column of a Dataframe, e.g.\r\n\r\n    df.nsmallest(n = 4, columns=df.columns).mean()\r\n\r\nThe result given by nsmallest will not give the proper value unless, as you well say, other strategy is used."
