    "body": "@daviddoji \r\n\r\n\r\nThis is correct, nsmallest is the smallest in the column ordering breaking ties, you prob want ``df.min()`` as @bobhaffner indicates\r\n```\r\nIn [7]: df.nsmallest(1, columns=df.columns)\r\nOut[7]: \r\n   a  b  c\r\n4 -1  6  3\r\n\r\nIn [8]: df\r\nOut[8]: \r\n    a  b   c\r\n0   1  9   2\r\n1   9  1   0\r\n2   8  2  19\r\n3  11  5   1\r\n4  -1  6   3\r\n5   6  0   2\r\n6   4  2   3\r\n7   9  3   2\r\n8   0  1   3\r\n\r\nIn [9]: df.min()\r\nOut[9]: \r\na   -1\r\nb    0\r\nc    0\r\ndtype: int64\r\n```"
  }
